3 "(e) Separate Fund for Line of Duty Death Benefits. – The Board of Trustees may make
4 additional funding available to the Department of State Treasurer to ensure the timely payment
5 of death benefits awarded by the Industrial Commission under the Public Safety Employees'
6 Death Benefits Act, Article 12A of Chapter 143 of the General Statutes, by depositing a
7 percentage of the State's employer contribution rate established for the benefits provided under
8 G.S. 135-165 into a separate fund from the Benefits Trust. This percentage shall not exceed four
9 hundredths percent (0.04%) in any given fiscal year. The Department of State Treasurer is
10 authorized to use the funds deposited into this separate fund for the sole purpose of paying for
11 death benefits awarded by the Industrial Commission under the Public Safety Employees' Death
12 Benefits Act and may do so only if all other State funds appropriated to the Department for the
13 fiscal year for the payment of those death benefits have been fully expended. Any funds deposited
14 by the Department of State Treasurer into a separate fund in accordance with this subsection that
15 remain unspent as of June 30 of the same fiscal year shall be transferred to the Benefit Fund as
16 an additional employer contribution."
17 SECTION 16.(b) This section becomes effective July 1, 2025.
